summary: This document contains various filings and certifications related to the Nine East 71st Street Corporation, including a subpoena for corporate records, a certificate of incorporation, and a certificate of dissolution. It highlights the involvement of Jeffrey Epstein and Darren K. Indyke in the corporation's management and legal compliance.

persons.name: Andrew M. Cuomo
persons.context: Mentioned as the Governor of New York in the context of the document's issuance.

persons.name: Rossana Rosado
persons.context: Identified as the Secretary of State of New York in the document.

persons.name: Brendan C. Hughes
persons.context: Signed the certification of the document as the Executive Deputy Secretary of State.

persons.name: Jeffrey E. Epstein
persons.context: Identified as the President of Nine East 71st Street Corporation.

persons.name: Darren K. Indyke
persons.context: Serves as the Secretary of Nine East 71st Street Corporation and is involved in legal filings.

connections.description: Epstein is the President and Indyke is the Secretary of the Nine East 71st Street Corporation.

events.title: Grand Jury Subpoena Issued
events.description: A subpoena was issued to the New York Department of State for corporate records related to Nine East 71st Street Corporation.

events.title: Dissolution of Nine East 71st Street Corporation
events.description: The corporation was dissolved by unanimous consent of the shareholders.

events.title: Consent to Dissolution
events.description: The New York State Department of Taxation and Finance consented to the dissolution of Nine East 71st Street Corporation.

keyFacts: The document includes a subpoena for corporate records related to Nine East 71st Street Corporation.
Jeffrey E. Epstein is identified as the President of Nine East 71st Street Corporation.
Darren K. Indyke is identified as the Secretary of Nine East 71st Street Corporation.
The corporation was dissolved in December 2012 by unanimous consent.
The New York State Department of Taxation and Finance consented to the dissolution of the corporation in April 2015.
